requirement_description: ​The Financial Management Division (FC) will continue to have a need for contractor support that will provide DEA overall with specialized experience and guidance in support of ongoing workplace reorganization and communication initiatives. requirement_title: Rescue One Contract for AED Program - HRES
requirement_description: DEA requires services to support the operation of DEA's Automatic External Defibrillator (AED) Program. This effort will include administrative support, physician medical direction, options for purchase of CPR and AED training, and assistance with logistics and loaner units in certain situations. DEA seeks a vendor that can adapt to the unique requirements of a Federal law enforcement agency in mission, authorities, and needs to maintain information security in order to successfully support DEA.

requirement_title: ODE Disaster Readiness Course (DRC) ESF-13 Training
requirement_description: DEA's Disaster Readiness Course (DRC) is a requirement for a training facility to conduct four days of training for DEA personnel who are likely to be deployed under the Department of Justice’s (DOJs) Emergency Support Function #13 (ESF #13). and #160;The ESF #13 Disaster Readiness Course (DRC) is designed to provide training and critical skills to prepare Special Agents for deployment to natural and man-made disasters in furtherance of response and recovery efforts. and #160;The DRC will prepare Special Agents with knowledge and training that will enable them to safely and effectively execute force-protection duties and other skills needed to be self-sufficient.

requirement_description: There are numerous novel psychoactive substances (NPS) being abused in the United States and they pose a significant risk to the public safety. To best protect the public from the dangers of these new drugs, the DEA needs to be able to not only obtain and study these emerging substances, but also study and evaluate the precursors and methodologies used to make these substances. The study and evaluation of the precursors and methodologies used to make these substances will enrich what is already known about how these substances are made and/or further support control actions to permanently place the precursors and/or substances under the Controlled Substances Act (CSA). This meets the goal of DEA and the Diversion Control Program.
